  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Nhs-funded Nursing Care - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
    <p>
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_nhs-funded_nursing_care">NHS-funded Nursing Care</xref>
 is an 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_activity_group">ACTIVITY GROUP</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
      <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_nhs-funded_nursing_care">NHS-funded Nursing Care</xref>
 (<xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_nhs-funded_nursing_care">NHS FNC</xref>) is funding provided by the NHS to a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_person">PERSON</xref>
 in a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_care_home_with_nursing">Care Home With Nursing</xref>
 who does not qualify for 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_nhs_continuing_healthcare">NHS Continuing Healthcare</xref>
 but has been assessed as requiring the services of a registered 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_nurse">NURSE</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
For further information on 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_nhs-funded_nursing_care">NHS-funded Nursing Care</xref>, see the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_department_of_health_and_social_care">Department of Health and Social Care</xref>
 part of the gov.uk website at: 
              <xref href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-framework-for-nhs-continuing-healthcare-and-nhs-funded-nursing-care" scope="external" format="html">National framework for NHS continuing healthcare and NHS-funded nursing care</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
